
Syntax: cflist add <conference> ...
        cflist delete <conference> ...
        cflist show
	cflist restart

Description: These commands are for ease of creating and maintaining a
   .cflist.  The first form adds conferences to your .cflist.  The
   second removes conferences from your .cflist, and the third form
   displays the current .cflist.  Finally the fourth form will join
   the first conference in your .cflist which has new information
   in it.

See also: 
   file cflist, check, next, change list 
